All frontend Javascript code will be exposed to the public. It is not the best place to hide secrets because anyone can see it.

Because you said that you are developing a library, you can make the secret key as a part of the parameters that should be provided by the user of that library, something like this:

```js
// someone using your library
yourLibrary({
  secretKey: &#39;someSecretKey&#39;
})
```

If this can&#39;t be an option for you, I think you have to store your secret key on a server elsewhere.

